You can try imaging the limelight again with your computer through balena etcher depending on which interface you’ll be using:

Limelight UI:

docs.limelightvision.io

Updating LimelightOS | Limelight Documentation

Follow this guide to update your Limelight Smart Camera to the latest version of LimelightOS.

Photonvision:

github.com/PhotonVision/photonvision

Create build for Limelight 3

opened 10:11PM - 13 Apr 23 UTC
srimanachanta
enhancement

Currently, users can use a Limelight 3 using the following steps. A build should… be generated along with the rest for Limelight. via @mcm001 steps 1. flash our stock Pi image (NOT limelight) 2. connect to the internet 3. run `sudo wget https://datasheets.raspberrypi.org/cmio/dt-blob-cam1.bin -O /boot/dt-blob.bin` 4. edit `/boot/config.txt` and uncomment `dtoverlay=ov5647`

P.d. If you’re using PV and you’ve never image your limelight on your own, it’s quite tricky so if you need anything I’m here to help

We also experienced this issue yesterday. It seems like one of the voltage regulators (on the 12V IN side) is fried. 23 Ohms between output and GND pins on the fried regulator, vs 47 kOhm on the POE side regulator. Thus providing an easy path for current to flow from the 5V rail to GND.
